So then just go for:

    1.37 ratio: 13.5" x 9.85"
    1.40 ratio: 13.5" x 9.64"
    1.42 ratio: 13.5" x 9.5"
    1.50 ratio: 13.5" x 9.0"

On Wed, 27 Jul 2005, Curt Sampson wrote:

> I originally said:
>     print on 11x14 to matt at about 34cm x 24cm for the han-kiri frame
> 
> But that was done calculating based on a han-kiri picture size, not the
> larger size of the frame.
> 
> The frame is about 388x482 (approx.)
> 
> So, to get six centimeter borders (which seem the nicest), we need 268 x
> 362.
> 
> But that's slightly larger than dai-yotsu-giri, so let's go for 7 cm
> borders, giving us 248 x 342. That gives us 3/4 cm. top and bottom of
> the print itself for borders, and an aspect ratio of 1.37, which is very
> nice.
> 
> If we wanted to get a narrow ratio, we can increase the long-side
> borders by a bit over the short side. To get 1.5, we need 228 x 342,
> giving us 8 cm borders: very nice!
